---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  lastUpdated="February 2026"
  description="Crawlix Accessibility Statement - Our commitment to making our software accessible to everyone."
>
  <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
  <p>
    Crawlix is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.
  </p>

  <h2>Standards We Follow</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to conform to the following accessibility standards:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> - Web Content Accessibility Guidelines</li>
    <li><strong>European Accessibility Act (EAA)</strong> - EU Directive 2019/882</li>
    <li><strong>Section 508</strong> - US accessibility requirements</li>
    <li><strong>EN 301 549</strong> - European accessibility standard for ICT products</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>

  <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>All functionality is accessible via keyboard</li>
    <li>Visible focus indicators for all interactive elements</li>
    <li>Logical tab order throughout the application</li>
    <li>Skip links to bypass repetitive content</li>
    <li>Keyboard shortcuts for common actions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Screen Reader Support</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Semantic HTML structure</li>
    <li>ARIA labels and descriptions where needed</li>
    <li>Live regions for dynamic content updates</li>
    <li>Proper heading hierarchy</li>
    <li>Meaningful link text</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Visual Accessibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Minimum 4.5:1 color contrast ratio for normal text</li>
    <li>Minimum 3:1 color contrast ratio for large text</li>
    <li>Information not conveyed by color alone</li>
    <li>Resizable text up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
    <li>Support for high contrast mode</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Motor Accessibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Large click targets (minimum 44x44 pixels)</li>
    <li>No time-limited interactions</li>
    <li>Reduced motion option respected</li>
    <li>No features requiring precise pointer movements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cognitive Accessibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Consistent navigation and layout</li>
    <li>Clear and simple language</li>
    <li>Error messages with clear guidance</li>
    <li>Confirmation dialogs for destructive actions</li>
    <li>Progress indicators for long operations</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Assistive Technology Compatibility</h2>
  <p>
    Crawlix has been tested with the following assistive technologies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>NVDA (Windows)</li>
    <li>VoiceOver (macOS)</li>
    <li>Orca (Linux)</li>
    <li>Windows High Contrast Mode</li>
    <li>macOS Increase Contrast</li>
    <li>Browser zoom up to 400%</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
  <p>
    We are aware of the following accessibility limitations and are working to address them:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Some third-party embedded content may not be fully accessible</li>
    <li>Complex data visualizations may be challenging for screen reader users (text alternatives provided)</li>
    <li>PDF exports may have limited accessibility features</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Testing and Auditing</h2>
  <p>
    We regularly test our application using:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Automated testing with axe-core</li>
    <li>Manual testing with screen readers</li>
    <li>Keyboard-only navigation testing</li>
    <li>Color contrast analyzers</li>
    <li>User testing with people with disabilities</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Feedback</h2>
  <p>
    We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of Crawlix. Please let us know if you encounter accessibility barriers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:accessibility@crawlix.app">accessibility@crawlix.app</a></li>
    <li>Response time: We aim to respond within 5 business days</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Enforcement Procedure</h2>
  <p>
    If you are not satisfied with our response to your accessibility feedback, you may contact your local enforcement body:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>EU:</strong> Your national equality body</li>
    <li><strong>UK:</strong> Equality Advisory Support Service (EASS)</li>
    <li><strong>US:</strong> Office for Civil Rights at the U.S. Department of Education</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
  <p>
    Accessibility of Crawlix relies on the following technologies:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>HTML5</li>
    <li>WAI-ARIA 1.2</li>
    <li>CSS</li>
    <li>JavaScript</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These technologies are relied upon for conformance with the accessibility standards used.
  </p>

  <h2>Assessment and Updates</h2>
  <p>
    This statement was last reviewed: February 2026
  </p>
  <p>
    We review our accessibility statement annually and update it whenever significant changes are made to the application.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
